Adults were collected from Taipei City Zoo, January 19, 2008 and transferred to the laboratory for rearing. Females began to deposit an average of 10-20 eggs in single egg mass (Fig. 
52A
) during middle March. Larvae hatched in 7 days. The larvae (Fig. 
52B
) fed on leaves and the larval duration was 14 days. mature larvae (Fig. 
52C
) burrowed into soil and built underground chambers for pupation. Duration of the pupal stage (Fig. 
52D
) was 28-30 days. Newly emerged adults (Fig. 
52E
) were yellowish brown and appeared during spring and were active (Fig. 
52F
). They became darker during summer and autumn and were inactive during winter.
